[32m│[0m ## SSRF Hostname Bypass Test Results                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I tested whether using "localhost" as a hostname can bypass the SSRF         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m restriction that blocked access to "127.0.0.1".                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Test Execution                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Command:**                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```bash                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m curl -X POST "http://127.0.0.1:33181/convert" -d                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "url=http://localhost:33181/admin" -s -v 2>&1                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Response:**                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application returns a **302 FOUND** redirect with a session cookie       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m containing the error message.                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Cookie Analysis                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m When decoding the session cookie from the response, it shows:                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```json                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m {                                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   "_flashes": [                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     {                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m       " t": [                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         "message",                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         "Error fetching the URL: <urlopen error  Connection refused>"        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m       ]                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     }                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   ]                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m }                                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Comparison: IP vs Hostname                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | Attempt | URL Payload | Result |                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m |---------|-------------|--------|                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | IP Address | `http://127.0.0.1:33181/admin` | Connection refused |         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | Hostname | `http://localhost:33181/admin` | **Connection refused** |       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Conclusion                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **The "localhost" hostname does NOT bypass the SSRF restriction.** Both      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m attempts result in the identical "Connection refused" error (errno 111),     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m indicating that:                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. The SSRF protection blocks all internal network requests regardless of    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m notation                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Both IP addresses (127.0.0.1) and hostnames (localhost) are treated       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m equally                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. The application attempts to fetch the URL but cannot establish a          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m connection to internal resources                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The SSRF protection appears to be robust and blocks requests to internal     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m resources using multiple addressing methods.                                 [32m│[0m
