[32m│[0m techniques to fingerprint the filter by observing which payloads bypass the  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m restriction.                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Critical Discovery**: The SSRF filter uses **naive string matching**       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m rather than proper IP resolution and validation.                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Filter Implementation Details                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Based on successful bypass using decimal IP representation, the filter       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m implementation appears to:                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **String-based blocking**: Only checks for literal strings "127.0.0.1"    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m and "localhost"                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **No IP resolution**: Does not resolve hostnames to IP addresses before   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m checking                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **No canonicalization**: Does not normalize different IP representations  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Single-layer validation**: Only performs one pass of string matching    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Successful Bypass Technique                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Decimal IP Representation**: `2130706433` (which equals 127.0.0.1)         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The filter blocks "127.0.0.1" but does NOT block the decimal equivalent    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - When the application resolves `http://2130706433`, it converts to          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 127.0.0.1                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - This allows accessing localhost resources through the SSRF                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Additional Bypass Vectors                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The same weakness would allow these bypasses:                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Octal: `0177.0.0.1`                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Hex: `0x7f.0x0.0x0.0x1`                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - IPv6: `::1`, `[::ffff:127.0.0.1]`                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Encoded: `127%2e0%2e0%2e1`                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Dword: `127.1`                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
